    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-01-27T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-01-27T05:00:00-05:00" n="90"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d90">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3652: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="#p_CES1"
                            type="from">Cunningham</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-27T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 27, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 27—7 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A Japanese member of the Municipal Council who usually acts as liaison officer
                    between the Japanese Naval Attaché and the Council has requested that a state of
                    emergency declaration should be issued today. <pb facs="0184" n="80"
                        xml:id="pg_80"/> The Secretary General promised to call a meeting of the
                    Municipal Council for the consideration of the request today.</p>
                <p>Repeated to the Legation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CES1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
